<headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 06 at 6:22PM CDT until July 06 at 7:30PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 730 PM CDT
FOR NORTH CENTRAL CARSON AND HUTCHINSON COUNTIES...
At 620 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles north of
Borger, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings.
Locations impacted include...
Borger, Fritch, Stinnett, Sanford and Pringle.
THUNDERSTORM DAMAGE THREAT...CONSIDERABLE
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...70 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
